1
00:00:00,203 --> 00:00:01,632
(We're in Gunsan, an island colony.)

2
00:00:01,633 --> 00:00:03,403
(Gogunsan Islands Race)

3
00:00:04,203 --> 00:00:06,873
(If they complete missions at each location...)

4
00:00:07,213 --> 00:00:08,873
(and reach the final spot before 1pm, )

5
00:00:09,313 --> 00:00:11,342
(their lunch is a west coast seafood camping meal.)

6
00:00:11,343 --> 00:00:13,423
(They lose 1 dish for every 5 minutes they're late.)

7
00:00:13,483 --> 00:00:15,483
(The race starts.)

8
00:00:15,713 --> 00:00:16,783
This is it.

9
00:00:17,323 --> 00:00:19,183
(Endless flour drop)

10
00:00:19,523 --> 00:00:20,622
(Focus, will you?)

11
00:00:20,623 --> 00:00:23,322
(Endless biking)

12
00:00:23,323 --> 00:00:24,392
Get it in one go!

13
00:00:24,393 --> 00:00:29,033
(The missions continue with barely time to catch a breath.)

14
00:00:29,093 --> 00:00:30,863
(How are we to do this?)

15
00:00:31,503 --> 00:00:32,503
Run.

16
00:00:32,504 --> 00:00:35,602
(An intense trip and breathtaking race)

17
00:00:35,603 --> 00:00:36,873
There's a lot here too!

18
00:00:37,273 --> 00:00:40,272
(What's the end result of the tough race?)

19
00:00:40,273 --> 00:00:41,273
It's done.

20
00:00:41,274 --> 00:00:42,742
(They arrive at 1:14pm.)

21
00:00:42,743 --> 00:00:45,813
(They win 3 out of 6 ingredients.)

22
00:00:47,553 --> 00:00:50,452
(At last, it's happy meal time.)

23
00:00:50,453 --> 00:00:51,523
Mayonnaise.

24
00:00:52,423 --> 00:00:55,423
(It wipes away the suffering they endured.)

25
00:00:56,193 --> 00:00:59,023
(What will happen after the cheerful meal?)

26
00:01:00,033 --> 00:01:03,902
(2 Days 1 Night)

27
00:01:03,903 --> 00:01:07,272
Look at the sea now. It's the prettiest time right now.

28
00:01:07,273 --> 00:01:08,373
Let's nap.

29
00:01:08,503 --> 00:01:10,173
- Take a nap.
- Yes, let's.

30
00:01:10,773 --> 00:01:11,773
Let's nap.

31
00:01:12,913 --> 00:01:14,973
Shall I take a poop next door?

32
00:01:16,173 --> 00:01:17,382
I can't stop farting.

33
00:01:17,383 --> 00:01:20,753
(Se Yoon ate too much and leaves to go to the toilet.)

34
00:01:23,253 --> 00:01:25,523
(Hesitating)

35
00:01:25,723 --> 00:01:28,423
(He found a mission card on the floor!)

36
00:01:31,223 --> 00:01:33,133
(What's this?)

37
00:01:34,263 --> 00:01:36,563
(Let's take it for now.)

38
00:01:37,463 --> 00:01:40,403
(He reads it in secret in a corner.)

39
00:01:40,703 --> 00:01:43,703
(Taking photos with his phone)

40
00:01:43,943 --> 00:01:46,413
(He suddenly runs!)

41
00:01:46,873 --> 00:01:48,273
Can I ride something? Like what?

42
00:01:48,943 --> 00:01:50,182
(He is...)

43
00:01:50,183 --> 00:01:51,842
(ready to go.)

44
00:01:51,843 --> 00:01:52,953
What a lucky break.

45
00:01:53,313 --> 00:01:55,753
I left to go to the toilet.

46
00:01:57,823 --> 00:01:58,982
How do I work this?

47
00:01:58,983 --> 00:02:00,453
(He's ready to go somewhere.)

48
00:02:00,953 --> 00:02:02,023
Gido Lighthouse?

49
00:02:02,623 --> 00:02:04,923
Gido Lighthouse? A red lighthouse.

50
00:02:06,933 --> 00:02:09,532
(Today's break-time hidden mission)

51
00:02:09,533 --> 00:02:11,032
(Gido Lighthouse grants wishes.)

52
00:02:11,033 --> 00:02:12,532
(The first to reach Gido Lighthouse and make a wish...)

53
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:13,932
(will be given a One-Bite Ticket.)

54
00:02:13,933 --> 00:02:15,332
(Just 1. 1st come, 1st served!)

55
00:02:15,333 --> 00:02:17,973
What a lucky break. This is insane.

56
00:02:18,643 --> 00:02:20,873
(To Se Yoon, "one bite...")

57
00:02:21,513 --> 00:02:22,673
Stick it in. Okay.

58
00:02:23,343 --> 00:02:26,213
(would be a meal to others.)

59
00:02:26,713 --> 00:02:30,082
(This is his chance to win dinner.)

60
00:02:30,083 --> 00:02:31,253
You fools.

61
00:02:31,953 --> 00:02:34,993
(4pm, Se Yoon leaves.)

62
00:02:35,523 --> 00:02:36,592
Let's go.

63
00:02:36,593 --> 00:02:37,822
(He left to go to the toilet, )

64
00:02:37,823 --> 00:02:39,499
(but now he's a strong contender to win one bite.)

65
00:02:39,523 --> 00:02:42,193
(Meanwhile, the other members...)

66
00:02:43,103 --> 00:02:45,233
(Relaxed and calm)

67
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:47,802
(They show no sign of leaving the room, )

68
00:02:47,803 --> 00:02:49,403
(so a crew member knocks on the door.)

69
00:02:49,943 --> 00:02:51,072
Do we have to go out?

70
00:02:51,073 --> 00:02:53,273
(Do we have to go out?)

71
00:02:54,913 --> 00:02:56,043
It's time already?

72
00:02:57,783 --> 00:03:02,453
(He goes outside to see what it's about.)

73
00:03:03,983 --> 00:03:07,523
(He finds the mission card Se Yoon left.)

74
00:03:08,123 --> 00:03:11,163
(He puts it in his pocket?)

75
00:03:11,893 --> 00:03:13,363
Where did Se Yoon go?

76
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:14,863
I don't know.

77
00:03:15,663 --> 00:03:16,903
He's not here.

78
00:03:17,463 --> 00:03:21,103
(He runs, just like Se Yoon!)

79
00:03:21,933 --> 00:03:24,603
(Can DinDin catch him up?)

80
00:03:25,403 --> 00:03:28,043
(DinDin leaves 15 minutes after Se Yoon.)

81
00:03:28,573 --> 00:03:31,083
(He kept the mission card.)

82
00:03:31,813 --> 00:03:34,353
(The others don't even get to read it.)

83
00:03:36,313 --> 00:03:37,623
This is why...

84
00:03:38,483 --> 00:03:39,923
you must never be lazy.

85
00:03:40,623 --> 00:03:42,492
Wait. When Se Yoon left to poop,

86
00:03:42,493 --> 00:03:43,613
did he go to the lighthouse?

87
00:03:44,763 --> 00:03:47,333
(Meanwhile, Se Yoon...)

88
00:03:49,563 --> 00:03:50,763
Is this the right way?

89
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:54,633
(Looking around)

90
00:03:55,073 --> 00:03:56,232
Where is it?

91
00:03:56,233 --> 00:03:58,472
(Where is Gido Lighthouse?)

92
00:03:58,473 --> 00:03:59,543
Gido Lighthouse?

93
00:04:00,313 --> 00:04:02,243
Where is it? This is madness.

94
00:04:02,843 --> 00:04:03,883
Gido Lighthouse.

95
00:04:05,083 --> 00:04:08,652
(Where on earth is Gido Lighthouse?)

96
00:04:08,653 --> 00:04:09,982
(Gido Lighthouse, base camp)

97
00:04:09,983 --> 00:04:13,753
(He's going the wrong way.)

98
00:04:13,953 --> 00:04:16,893
Will I end up on the freeway?

99
00:04:17,493 --> 00:04:19,092
Where is Gido Lighthouse?

100
00:04:19,093 --> 00:04:20,292
(He senses something's wrong, but pushes on.)

101
00:04:20,293 --> 00:04:21,333
I should ask.

102
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:23,833
Where are you?

103
00:04:24,163 --> 00:04:25,863
Gido Lighthouse is up here.

104
00:04:26,063 --> 00:04:28,503
Where am I right now?

105
00:04:29,403 --> 00:04:30,543
Where am I on the map?

106
00:04:31,743 --> 00:04:33,142
Where is Gido Lighthouse?

107
00:04:33,143 --> 00:04:35,473
(Unlike smart DinDin who consults his phone map, )

108
00:04:36,243 --> 00:04:37,312
I go back...

109
00:04:37,313 --> 00:04:38,912
(Se Yoon uses an analog option.)

110
00:04:38,913 --> 00:04:41,183
Where am I now? It looks like Jangja Island.

111
00:04:42,153 --> 00:04:43,383
It's a dead end.

112
00:04:45,123 --> 00:04:46,692
Gido Lighthouse, red bridge.

113
00:04:46,693 --> 00:04:48,423
(DinDin might catch up!)

114
00:04:48,723 --> 00:04:50,663
I'm bad with directions. This is crazy.

115
00:04:51,793 --> 00:04:52,823
Where...

116
00:04:53,793 --> 00:04:55,073
It's right behind where we were.

117
00:04:55,293 --> 00:04:56,562
Let's go. Get on quick.

118
00:04:56,563 --> 00:04:57,863
(He located the lighthouse!)

119
00:04:58,503 --> 00:04:59,902
I'm done for.

120
00:04:59,903 --> 00:05:01,303
(He rushes back the way he came.)

121
00:05:01,933 --> 00:05:02,973
Darn it.

122
00:05:03,743 --> 00:05:04,943
What are you doing?

123
00:05:06,303 --> 00:05:09,713
(Meanwhile, in the room of rest)

124
00:05:11,283 --> 00:05:14,583
(He senses something is off!)

125
00:05:14,713 --> 00:05:15,883
- Jong Min.
- Is it time?

126
00:05:17,223 --> 00:05:18,252
What is it?

127
00:05:18,253 --> 00:05:20,352
(He doesn't know the mission because DinDin's a thief.)

128
00:05:20,353 --> 00:05:21,623
- What is it?
- What's up?

129
00:05:21,953 --> 00:05:23,023
You told us to rest.

130
00:05:23,963 --> 00:05:25,293
- What is it?
- What's this?

131
00:05:27,063 --> 00:05:28,892
(Whatever it is, let's run!)

132
00:05:28,893 --> 00:05:29,933
What is it?

133
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:32,002
(On 2 Days 1 Night, )

134
00:05:32,003 --> 00:05:33,003
Just like that?

135
00:05:33,004 --> 00:05:34,572
(if one runs, everyone runs.)

136
00:05:34,573 --> 00:05:36,673
What's wrong? What is it?

137
00:05:37,673 --> 00:05:38,902
Where are the other two?

138
00:05:38,903 --> 00:05:40,412
(The rest can't tell what's going on.)

139
00:05:40,413 --> 00:05:41,513
Where are the others?

140
00:05:42,343 --> 00:05:43,443
You told us to rest.

141
00:05:43,983 --> 00:05:45,743
I left you a hint to read,

142
00:05:46,083 --> 00:05:47,713
but DinDin ran away with it.

143
00:05:47,983 --> 00:05:50,183
- Darn it.
- Give him a call.

144
00:05:51,283 --> 00:05:53,192
- What is he doing?
- What is he doing?

145
00:05:53,193 --> 00:05:55,853
- It's not a team thing?
- He really...

146
00:05:56,053 --> 00:05:57,163
We're a team.

147
00:05:57,423 --> 00:05:59,862
(Calling DinDin the thief)

148
00:05:59,863 --> 00:06:01,293
Tell him to change the song.

149
00:06:02,233 --> 00:06:04,202
- What?
- What are you doing?

150
00:06:04,203 --> 00:06:06,362
- What do you mean?
- We're a team.

151
00:06:06,363 --> 00:06:08,403
- Why are you doing this?
- Where are you?

152
00:06:09,073 --> 00:06:11,143
- Where do you think?
- Where are you?

153
00:06:11,743 --> 00:06:13,243
We're still here, of course.

154
00:06:14,343 --> 00:06:16,312
We're nearby.

155
00:06:16,313 --> 00:06:17,482
(Just then, an electric vehicle goes by.)

156
00:06:17,483 --> 00:06:18,612
You're nearby?

157
00:06:18,613 --> 00:06:21,452
(I'm passing by.)

158
00:06:21,453 --> 00:06:24,183
- You're nearby?
- Yes, near the camp.

159
00:06:24,583 --> 00:06:26,282
(I think something went by.)

160
00:06:26,283 --> 00:06:27,623
- What?
- Bye for now.

161
00:06:27,853 --> 00:06:29,422
Let's ask the helicam guy.

162
00:06:29,423 --> 00:06:30,862
- I asked.
- Get him to find them.

163
00:06:30,863 --> 00:06:33,462
You're right. We can find them with the helicam.

164
00:06:33,463 --> 00:06:34,463
But...

165
00:06:34,993 --> 00:06:36,902
(The three fools embark on a mission to find the thief.)

166
00:06:36,903 --> 00:06:38,663
Do you see them?

167
00:06:38,803 --> 00:06:39,832
Is that a person?

168
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:40,902
(Featuring the heli guy)

169
00:06:40,903 --> 00:06:42,533
Where is this place anyway?

170
00:06:42,673 --> 00:06:43,973
Someone's in a car.

171
00:06:45,473 --> 00:06:46,813
Can you see anything on this?

172
00:06:49,043 --> 00:06:50,383
The drone is over there?

173
00:06:50,613 --> 00:06:52,882
It's that yellow thing. Do you see it?

174
00:06:52,883 --> 00:06:54,283
It's over there. Let's go that way.

175
00:06:55,253 --> 00:06:58,223
(Seon Ho finds the action near the yellow crane suspicious.)

176
00:06:58,753 --> 00:07:02,822
(It happens to be right next to the lighthouse!)

177
00:07:02,823 --> 00:07:03,862
You want to go that far?

178
00:07:03,863 --> 00:07:05,322
- It's too far.
- It's too far.

179
00:07:05,323 --> 00:07:07,663
Hey. This is my car. Let's go.

180
00:07:08,393 --> 00:07:10,202
- Can't we ride that?
- Your manager is in the car.

181
00:07:10,203 --> 00:07:11,362
- Let's get in.
- Let's get in.

182
00:07:11,363 --> 00:07:12,532
Can't we take the car?

183
00:07:12,533 --> 00:07:14,472
- Hello.
- Get in already.

184
00:07:14,473 --> 00:07:15,502
Let's go to the yellow thing.

185
00:07:15,503 --> 00:07:16,972
- Get in the front.
- No directions?

186
00:07:16,973 --> 00:07:18,073
- Just go.
- Let's go.

187
00:07:18,503 --> 00:07:20,943
I can't sit in the passenger seat.

188
00:07:21,513 --> 00:07:22,773
We'll go without you, then.

189
00:07:23,583 --> 00:07:24,912
- We'll call you.
- Let's go.

190
00:07:24,913 --> 00:07:26,482
- Why would you call?
- We'll call.

191
00:07:26,483 --> 00:07:28,552
- We won't betray you.
- Okay.

192
00:07:28,553 --> 00:07:29,612
- Don't betray me.
- We won't.

193
00:07:29,613 --> 00:07:30,722
- Get DinDin.
- Okay.

194
00:07:30,723 --> 00:07:31,923
- Call me.
- Okay.

195
00:07:32,553 --> 00:07:34,522
- Call me!
- Okay. We'll get him.

196
00:07:34,523 --> 00:07:35,852
- Get him.
- We will.

197
00:07:35,853 --> 00:07:37,339
(A car might be faster than an electric vehicle!)

198
00:07:37,363 --> 00:07:39,323
- What is this?
- What is this? It was our break.

199
00:07:40,233 --> 00:07:41,633
- Keep observing your side.
- Okay.

200
00:07:41,893 --> 00:07:43,739
- You take the left side.
- Keep observing your side.

201
00:07:43,763 --> 00:07:45,363
Where are we? It's quite close.

202
00:07:46,163 --> 00:07:47,723
Our cameramen are there. So it means...

203
00:07:48,003 --> 00:07:50,543
(Meanwhile, Se Yoon and DinDin...)

204
00:07:51,373 --> 00:07:52,672
I think I'm back to the starting point.

205
00:07:52,673 --> 00:07:54,433
(are getting closer to the Gido Lighthouse.)

206
00:07:54,673 --> 00:07:56,712
It's over there. My gosh, there it is.

207
00:07:56,713 --> 00:07:58,433
(The red lighthouse is seen at a distance.)

208
00:07:59,213 --> 00:08:00,213
That's the one.

209
00:08:00,214 --> 00:08:01,759
(DinDin also spots the Gido Lighthouse.)

210
00:08:01,783 --> 00:08:04,423
(Which one of them will arrive first at the lighthouse?)

211
00:08:04,653 --> 00:08:06,382
- Is it over there?
- Yes. The motorcycle is here.

212
00:08:06,383 --> 00:08:07,452
The motorcycle is here.

213
00:08:07,453 --> 00:08:08,852
People are inside.

214
00:08:08,853 --> 00:08:10,373
(The thief catchers are chasing them.)

215
00:08:10,663 --> 00:08:13,292
(They're heading to the lighthouse from three different directions.)

216
00:08:13,293 --> 00:08:14,863
(Gido Lighthouse, the break room)

217
00:08:15,093 --> 00:08:17,763
(A sudden mission, One-Bite Race)

218
00:08:18,103 --> 00:08:24,443
(Only one of them will win a chance to have a bite.)

219
00:08:25,673 --> 00:08:27,272
- Please.
- Please.

220
00:08:27,273 --> 00:08:28,812
- This isn't a break.
- Please.

221
00:08:28,813 --> 00:08:32,613
(What's the final result of the One-Bite Race?)

222
00:08:33,183 --> 00:08:35,152
(At that time, a member approaches the lighthouse first.)

223
00:08:35,153 --> 00:08:37,923
(Is it Se Yoon?)

224
00:08:38,583 --> 00:08:39,923
I want to have dinner.

225
00:08:40,923 --> 00:08:42,123
Please let me have a bite.

226
00:08:43,923 --> 00:08:45,163
Am I first? Really?

227
00:08:46,593 --> 00:08:47,662
What's going on?

228
00:08:47,663 --> 00:08:49,332
(Joon and Seon Ho arrive rather late.)

229
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:50,363
What is it?

230
00:08:51,763 --> 00:08:52,932
It's over?

231
00:08:52,933 --> 00:08:54,872
(Did Se Yoon win the race?)

232
00:08:54,873 --> 00:08:57,643
One bite.

233
00:08:58,473 --> 00:09:02,143
(DinDin who's been hiding emerges out.)

234
00:09:03,173 --> 00:09:05,082
(Se Yoon also didn't make it.)

235
00:09:05,083 --> 00:09:06,313
How did you know, by the way?

236
00:09:06,483 --> 00:09:08,653
- What's going on?
- It's over?

237
00:09:09,053 --> 00:09:10,123
Really? Darn it.

238
00:09:10,623 --> 00:09:12,383
I want to have dinner.

239
00:09:13,453 --> 00:09:15,492
Please let me have a bite.

240
00:09:15,493 --> 00:09:17,823
(DinDin managed to make a wish before Se Yoon.)

241
00:09:18,763 --> 00:09:20,763
(DinDin wins the One-Bite Ticket.)

242
00:09:21,533 --> 00:09:23,933
When I came out to take a dump, I saw the mission card then.

243
00:09:24,303 --> 00:09:25,303
What about Jong Min?

244
00:09:25,304 --> 00:09:27,802
We didn't have space for him in the car.

245
00:09:27,803 --> 00:09:29,683
So he's waiting for us. We're on the same team.

246
00:09:30,673 --> 00:09:33,143
What's going on? I just don't understand this.

247
00:09:34,573 --> 00:09:36,043
I don't understand this game.

248
00:09:37,543 --> 00:09:39,483
- It's Jong Min.
- Jong Min.

249
00:09:40,113 --> 00:09:41,412
Hey. What are you guys doing?

250
00:09:41,413 --> 00:09:44,623
If you don't hurry over here, you'll be in danger, Jong Min.

251
00:09:45,253 --> 00:09:46,253
No.

252
00:09:46,993 --> 00:09:48,422
You'll end up on a fishing boat.

253
00:09:48,423 --> 00:09:50,293
No. They told me to rest.

254
00:09:51,193 --> 00:09:53,363
Jong Min, you'll be in trouble.

255
00:09:53,793 --> 00:09:54,863
What's going on?

256
00:09:55,493 --> 00:09:56,762
What is this?

257
00:09:56,763 --> 00:09:58,132
(Something about this feels chilling and ominous.)

258
00:09:58,133 --> 00:09:59,133
Is it true?

259
00:09:59,803 --> 00:10:00,932
Should I go then?

260
00:10:00,933 --> 00:10:02,572
(The mission is over now...)

261
00:10:02,573 --> 00:10:03,573
(when he's still clueless.)

262
00:10:03,574 --> 00:10:04,603
Is it over?

263
00:10:05,403 --> 00:10:08,372
You can be at the base camp with the electric vehicle.

264
00:10:08,373 --> 00:10:09,413
Okay.

265
00:10:09,673 --> 00:10:10,842
Hey, we managed.

266
00:10:10,843 --> 00:10:12,613
