The members who lost must be sad.

1278
00:45:34,573 --> 00:45:36,472
- I'm so sad.
- You lost by a small margin.

1279
00:45:36,473 --> 00:45:38,612
Although you lost, you worked hard as well.

1280
00:45:38,613 --> 00:45:39,613
We worked really hard.

1281
00:45:39,614 --> 00:45:40,942
So we prepared a special dish of Gunsan for you.

1282
00:45:40,943 --> 00:45:42,442
- That sounds great.
- Nice.

1283
00:45:42,443 --> 00:45:44,412
- We'll serve you the special dish.
- Gunsan's special dish.

1284
00:45:44,413 --> 00:45:45,653
Gunsan's special dish.

1285
00:45:45,753 --> 00:45:46,753
- What is that?
- What is it?

1286
00:45:46,754 --> 00:45:47,914
(The losers' meal is served.)

1287
00:45:47,953 --> 00:45:50,052
- What's this?
- Is it pickled radish?

1288
00:45:50,053 --> 00:45:51,552
It's pickled uloe.

1289
00:45:51,553 --> 00:45:52,622
- Uloe?
- Yes.

1290
00:45:52,623 --> 00:45:55,392
- Uloe?
- It's similar to Korean melon.

1291
00:45:55,393 --> 00:45:57,692
Over 70 percent the uloe produced in the whole country...

1292
00:45:57,693 --> 00:45:59,962
is produced in Gunsan.

1293
00:45:59,963 --> 00:46:01,503
- Ulhoe?
- It's "uloe."

1294
00:46:02,433 --> 00:46:03,502
It looks tasty.

1295
00:46:03,503 --> 00:46:05,073
(Tasting)

1296
00:46:05,473 --> 00:46:07,502
(What? It's delicious.)

1297
00:46:07,503 --> 00:46:08,503
- It's good.
- What's this?

1298
00:46:08,504 --> 00:46:09,612
It'd be good if we mix it with rice...

1299
00:46:09,613 --> 00:46:11,812
- and a bit of sesame oil.
- Each of you can take one.

1300
00:46:11,813 --> 00:46:12,883
- It's good.
- Oh, my.

1301
00:46:13,583 --> 00:46:15,642
This is crazy good. It's the taste I've never tried before.

1302
00:46:15,643 --> 00:46:16,882
(They're not interested at all.)

1303
00:46:16,883 --> 00:46:17,913
- It's mine.
- Come on.

1304
00:46:18,153 --> 00:46:19,223
Goodness, it's so salty.

1305
00:46:20,883 --> 00:46:22,422
I'll eat it with some rice. It's too salty.

1306
00:46:22,423 --> 00:46:24,423
(Since it's pickled, it's too salty without rice.)

1307
00:46:26,323 --> 00:46:28,122
DinDin, you gained...

1308
00:46:28,123 --> 00:46:29,462
the One-Bite Ticket.

1309
00:46:29,463 --> 00:46:32,332
We thought a normal spoon would be too small,

1310
00:46:32,333 --> 00:46:33,562
so we prepared two types of spoon.

1311
00:46:33,563 --> 00:46:34,563
(Big spoons for one bite)

1312
00:46:34,564 --> 00:46:35,932
Those spoons are so big.

1313
00:46:35,933 --> 00:46:37,173
It should be enough.

1314
00:46:37,933 --> 00:46:39,843
The natural taste of it is awesome.

1315
00:46:40,003 --> 00:46:41,773
- DinDin... Hey.
- You'll eat that much?

1316
00:46:42,973 --> 00:46:44,519
- You can eat them all?
- He took all the cockles.

1317
00:46:44,543 --> 00:46:46,083
You'll eat... What are you doing?

1318
00:46:46,283 --> 00:46:47,682
- Hey!
- Why?

1319
00:46:47,683 --> 00:46:48,912
Gosh, seriously.

1320
00:46:48,913 --> 00:46:50,312
It'll become tough, DinDin.

1321
00:46:50,313 --> 00:46:51,689
You'll be criticized if you eat it like that.

1322
00:46:51,713 --> 00:46:52,859
It won't be tasty if you eat it that way.

1323
00:46:52,883 --> 00:46:53,982
I have four of them.

1324
00:46:53,983 --> 00:46:55,122
The heat is too low.

1325
00:46:55,123 --> 00:46:56,322
I'll put them on the spoon first.

1326
00:46:56,323 --> 00:46:57,552
(He starts putting them on the spoon.)

1327
00:46:57,553 --> 00:46:58,823
My, this is amazing.

1328
00:46:59,053 --> 00:47:00,862
- And then...
- That should be tasty enough.

1329
00:47:00,863 --> 00:47:02,893
But I don't think... Can he eat it all at once?

1330
00:47:03,363 --> 00:47:04,662
You're not allowed to eat what you drop.

1331
00:47:04,663 --> 00:47:05,692
If you drop something, give it to Jong Min.

1332
00:47:05,693 --> 00:47:07,233
Sounds good. I hope he drops a lot.

1333
00:47:07,303 --> 00:47:08,623
He'll put some more on the spoon.

1334
00:47:09,273 --> 00:47:10,473
He can eat it all?

1335
00:47:10,833 --> 00:47:12,902
- No way. He has a small mouth.
- Will you be okay?

1336
00:47:12,903 --> 00:47:14,303
Put this plate under it.

1337
00:47:14,543 --> 00:47:15,779
- You might spill some.
- I'm not sure if he can eat it all.

1338
00:47:15,803 --> 00:47:17,713
- Will you eat what I drop?
- Yes.

1339
00:47:18,173 --> 00:47:19,283
Drop just one of them.

1340
00:47:19,383 --> 00:47:20,412
- Just one?
- Yes.

1341
00:47:20,413 --> 00:47:21,889
You don't mind if it comes back out of my mouth?

1342
00:47:21,913 --> 00:47:22,913
- Well, okay.
- Really?

1343
00:47:22,914 --> 00:47:24,012
(Laughing)

1344
00:47:24,013 --> 00:47:25,213
- "Okay?"
- Okay.

1345
00:47:25,783 --> 00:47:27,152
- Okay.
- Just one bite, please.

1346
00:47:27,153 --> 00:47:28,453
(DinDin will have one bite.)

1347
00:47:28,623 --> 00:47:31,223
(It's a big bite. He must never have had such a big bite before.)

1348
00:47:31,293 --> 00:47:32,763
(Taking a deep breath first)

1349
00:47:33,093 --> 00:47:34,322
(He opens his mouth widely to put all the food in his mouth.)

1350
00:47:34,323 --> 00:47:35,922
- I think he'll eat it all at once.
- He's going to spill some.

1351
00:47:35,923 --> 00:47:37,683
Oh, no. He dropped a piece of water parsley.

1352
00:47:38,333 --> 00:47:40,503
(He only dropped a piece of water parsley.)

1353
00:47:40,633 --> 00:47:41,932
(He managed to cram 4 cockles in his small mouth.)

1354
00:47:41,933 --> 00:47:43,233
Forget it. I won't eat it.

1355
00:47:43,673 --> 00:47:45,072
We should give him some time to savor it.

1356
00:47:45,073 --> 00:47:46,619
(How heartless. He put them all in his mouth.)

1357
00:47:46,643 --> 00:47:47,643
(Spinning his spoon while exclaiming with satisfaction)

1358
00:47:47,644 --> 00:47:49,102
(Spinning his spoon while exclaiming with satisfaction)

1359
00:47:49,103 --> 00:47:51,312
The texture is amazing.

1360
00:47:51,313 --> 00:47:53,642
- Right?
- Clams usually smell a bit fishy,

1361
00:47:53,643 --> 00:47:54,943
but this one doesn't.

1362
00:47:55,383 --> 00:47:58,453
It's like one of the White Spoon chefs on "Culinary Class Wars."

1363
00:47:58,753 --> 00:48:01,193
You can make it to the third round with the ingredient alone.

1364
00:48:01,723 --> 00:48:03,122
That was a hearty meal.

1365
00:48:03,123 --> 00:48:04,422
You finished the food so quickly.

1366
00:48:04,423 --> 00:48:05,622
It was really good.

1367
00:48:05,623 --> 00:48:06,623
They seem really satisfied.

1368
00:48:06,624 --> 00:48:08,463
Life is simple.

1369
00:48:08,593 --> 00:48:11,862
- A good meal made me happy.
- Exactly.

1370
00:48:11,863 --> 00:48:13,702
It was good, but we'll be able to see our breath outside shortly.

1371
00:48:13,703 --> 00:48:14,902
(He's worried as it's time for Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors.)

1372
00:48:14,903 --> 00:48:16,072
I think we'll play a game outside.

1373
00:48:16,073 --> 00:48:17,372
- Thank you for the food.
- You're welcome.

1374
00:48:17,373 --> 00:48:19,293
- I really enjoyed it.
- Thank you for the food.

1375
00:48:20,343 --> 00:48:22,503
(The school building is surrounded by pitch darkness.)

1376
00:48:25,343 --> 00:48:28,583
(Suddenly, one classroom is lit up?)

1377
00:48:28,913 --> 00:48:32,013
(After the last graduation ceremony, the classroom was cleaned.)

1378
00:48:33,723 --> 00:48:35,223
- Can I keep my shoes on?
- Yes.

1379
00:48:36,953 --> 00:48:38,729
- Can we keep our shoes on?
- It's a music room.

1380
00:48:38,753 --> 00:48:40,592
Many of us are musicians.

1381
00:48:40,593 --> 00:48:41,662
Can I have some cool water?

1382
00:48:41,663 --> 00:48:43,032
(The members enter with suspicion.)

1383
00:48:43,033 --> 00:48:45,073
What place is this? What kind of classroom is this?

1384
00:48:45,163 --> 00:48:46,303
It says it's a music room.

1385
00:48:46,463 --> 00:48:47,463
Is it written?

1386
00:48:47,833 --> 00:48:50,472
We'll begin Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors.

1387
00:48:50,473 --> 00:48:51,773
- Great.
- All right.

1388
00:48:52,503 --> 00:48:54,202
Do you guys remember...

1389
00:48:54,203 --> 00:48:57,542
the fierce competition in the midst of suspenseful tension...

1390
00:48:57,543 --> 00:48:58,543
you had in Uiryeong?

1391
00:48:58,613 --> 00:48:59,642
- What was it?
- What was it?

1392
00:48:59,643 --> 00:49:00,683
The ogre game.

1393
00:49:00,943 --> 00:49:02,043
What do you mean?

1394
00:49:02,643 --> 00:49:04,353
- What's the ogre game?
- Oh, that.

1395
00:49:04,513 --> 00:49:05,513
What's the ogre game?

1396
00:49:05,514 --> 00:49:07,253
The one where you hit others with a club.

1397
00:49:08,883 --> 00:49:10,793
(It took place in a dark room with no light.)

1398
00:49:11,053 --> 00:49:13,993
(The suspenseful moment of life and death)

1399
00:49:14,423 --> 00:49:17,063
(The Ogre's Club game in the darkness)

1400
00:49:17,263 --> 00:49:19,403
Today's Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors is...

1401
00:49:19,433 --> 00:49:21,963
Upgraded Ogre's Club.

1402
00:49:22,773 --> 00:49:24,572
The lights will be off without a warning.

1403
00:49:24,573 --> 00:49:26,242
(The classroom gets dark at random timing as soon as the game begins.)

1404
00:49:26,243 --> 00:49:28,072
You have to find the ogre's club in the dark...

1405
00:49:28,073 --> 00:49:30,043
and touch another member with it.

1406
00:49:30,843 --> 00:49:33,512
The first member to be hit with the ogre's club...

1407
00:49:33,513 --> 00:49:35,413
will sleep outdoors.

1408
00:49:35,983 --> 00:49:38,182
As you must remember, you're allowed to move...

1409
00:49:38,183 --> 00:49:39,423
only when the lights are off.

1410
00:49:40,083 --> 00:49:42,152
If the member with the ogre's club...

1411
00:49:42,153 --> 00:49:43,952
moves when the lights are on,

1412
00:49:43,953 --> 00:49:45,352
he must put the club down right away.

1413
00:49:45,353 --> 00:49:47,093
(You must return the club immediately.)

1414
00:49:47,293 --> 00:49:49,963
- I said the game had been upgraded.
- Yes.

1415
00:49:50,063 --> 00:49:51,333
In the upgraded game,

1416
00:49:51,663 --> 00:49:53,062
the ogre must walk around on one foot.

1417
00:49:53,063 --> 00:49:54,262
(In the upgraded version, the ogre must walk on one foot.)

1418
00:49:54,263 --> 00:49:56,273
- It sounds difficult.
- The ogre has one leg.

1419
00:49:56,833 --> 00:49:58,672
- So we should hop like this?
- That's correct.

1420
00:49:58,673 --> 00:49:59,702
(The ogre can only move on one foot.)

1421
00:49:59,703 --> 00:50:00,703
This will be hard.

1422
00:50:00,773 --> 00:50:02,812
The other members can use both legs, right?

1423
00:50:02,813 --> 00:50:03,813
- That's right.
- The rest can walk on both feet.

1424
00:50:03,814 --> 00:50:05,414
- The rest can walk on both feet?
- Yes.

1425
00:50:05,443 --> 00:50:07,512
Those who run away from the ogre are at an advantage.

1426
00:50:07,513 --> 00:50:08,642
(It became more difficult to play the role of the ogre.)

1427
00:50:08,643 --> 00:50:09,763
I don't want to be the ogre.

1428
00:50:10,513 --> 00:50:13,782
We'll continue the game until we have three losers.

1429
00:50:13,783 --> 00:50:14,952
(Only 2 members can sleep indoors. Who will survive?)

1430
00:50:14,953 --> 00:50:16,522
- Can I just keep running away?
- We don't know where it is.

1431
00:50:16,523 --> 00:50:18,452
You'll throw it in a random direction? Okay.

1432
00:50:18,453 --> 00:50:19,699
(It begins when the lights are off and Director Joo throws the club.)

1433
00:50:19,723 --> 00:50:22,004
- Put your hand on the wall.
- Put your hand on the wall.

1434
00:50:22,663 --> 00:50:24,092
(Standing far away from the wall)

1435
00:50:24,093 --> 00:50:25,792
Gosh, just stand straight.

1436
00:50:25,793 --> 00:50:27,432
You can reach only this far, right? I can reach this far.

1437
00:50:27,433 --> 00:50:28,533
(I can reach this far.)

1438
00:50:28,963 --> 00:50:30,103
(Laughing)

1439
00:50:30,403 --> 00:50:32,602
I guess you want to sleep outside tonight.

1440
00:50:32,603 --> 00:50:34,603
- Oh, they got into a fight.
- Okay. Let's go.

1441
00:50:34,743 --> 00:50:36,512
- Let's see which one of you...
- I'll catch DinDin first.

1442
00:50:36,513 --> 00:50:37,773
- will win.
- Okay.

1443
00:50:38,413 --> 00:50:39,442
I'm already nervous. Gosh.

1444
00:50:39,443 --> 00:50:41,343
(Nervous)

1445
00:50:41,513 --> 00:50:43,483
- One, two, three.
- Run!

1446
00:50:44,953 --> 00:50:48,223
(The club flies into the air.)

1447
00:50:51,523 --> 00:50:54,363
(Se Yoon got the club.)

1448
00:50:54,663 --> 00:50:58,163
(The fatty ogre starts moving.)

1449
00:50:59,633 --> 00:51:02,063
(Both the ogre and survivors can move only when it's dark.)

1450
00:51:02,633 --> 00:51:05,903
(The fatty ogre moves forward on one foot.)

1451
00:51:06,273 --> 00:51:10,443
(Fearful)

1452
00:51:15,343 --> 00:51:17,183
(No way.)

1453
00:51:21,053 --> 00:51:22,082
What is he doing?

1454
00:51:22,083 --> 00:51:23,793
(He lost his footing.)

1455
00:51:24,323 --> 00:51:29,123
(Walking on 1 foot is hard for the man weighing 126kg.)

1456
00:51:29,393 --> 00:51:32,033
(Where is the club?)

1457
00:51:32,963 --> 00:51:34,303
What do you want to do?

1458
00:51:34,833 --> 00:51:37,103
What do you want to do, Se Yoon?

1459
00:51:37,773 --> 00:51:39,172
- Spare me, please.
- Shall I?

1460
00:51:39,173 --> 00:51:40,372
- Spare me.
- Shall I?

1461
00:51:40,373 --> 00:51:41,903
- Spare me just once.
- Okay.

1462
00:51:42,203 --> 00:51:43,272
I'll let you live.

1463
00:51:43,273 --> 00:51:44,342
(The Din-ogre is like a duck to water.)

1464
00:51:44,343 --> 00:51:46,023
- Are you okay?
- Come on, you guys. Move.

1465
00:51:47,213 --> 00:51:51,553
I don't see Jong Min.

1466
00:51:51,683 --> 00:51:52,782
Where is he?

1467
00:51:52,783 --> 00:51:54,053
- It's weird.
- He's there.

1468
00:51:54,153 --> 00:51:55,552
- He's right there.
- He's right there.

1469
00:51:55,553 --> 00:51:56,693
You can fight him 1-on-1.

1470
00:51:56,793 --> 00:51:58,752
(Enemies are everywhere.)

1471
00:51:58,753 --> 00:51:59,763
You can fight him 1-on-1.

1472
00:52:00,163 --> 00:52:03,363
(Is that right?)

1473
00:52:03,833 --> 00:52:06,663
(Jong Min is trapped in the corner.)

1474
00:52:06,833 --> 00:52:07,962
You can fight him 1-on-1.

1475
00:52:07,963 --> 00:52:11,303
(When it gets dark, Din-ogre attacks him.)

1476
00:52:11,573 --> 00:52:14,303
(Will Jong Min be out just like this?)

1477
00:52:15,043 --> 00:52:16,143
He's here.

1478
00:52:18,613 --> 00:52:19,743
Hit him.

1479
00:52:19,943 --> 00:52:23,553
(He barely managed to dodge the club.)

1480
00:52:23,783 --> 00:52:26,253
(Relieved)

1481
00:52:27,023 --> 00:52:33,563
(After facing a crisis, Jong Min runs farther away.)

1482
00:52:33,693 --> 00:52:35,693
(Right then)

1483
00:52:36,763 --> 00:52:39,963
(DinDin loses his balance?)

1484
00:52:40,103 --> 00:52:43,533
(He'll be fine if he keeps his foot on the ground.)

1485
00:52:43,833 --> 00:52:46,843
(Twisting his body)

1486
00:52:48,373 --> 00:52:49,772
(Din-ogre's leg is reaching its limits.)

1487
00:52:49,773 --> 00:52:50,933
Impressive. He's holding out.

1488
00:52:53,083 --> 00:52:55,082
(Edgy)

1489
00:52:55,083 --> 00:52:56,143
I'm so tired.

1490
00:52:57,213 --> 00:52:58,353
I'm exhausted.

1491
00:52:59,783 --> 00:53:06,693
(I must end this now.)

1492
00:53:07,093 --> 00:53:10,993
Why are you targeting only me?

1493
00:53:11,933 --> 00:53:13,002
Oh, boy. He'll fail.

1494
00:53:13,003 --> 00:53:14,333
(Staggering)

1495
00:53:15,033 --> 00:53:17,203
Look here. Joon is here.

1496
00:53:19,133 --> 00:53:20,572
(He changes the target.)

1497
00:53:20,573 --> 00:53:21,773
- I'm sorry.
- What?

1498
00:53:22,003 --> 00:53:24,112
(What? Me?)

1499
00:53:24,113 --> 00:53:26,042
- Kill him. Kill anyone. Good.
- He's out.

1500
00:53:26,043 --> 00:53:27,243
- No.
- Kill him.

1501
00:53:27,943 --> 00:53:30,552
- No. The lights were on.
- It's over.

1502
00:53:30,553 --> 00:53:31,912
Joon, you're out.

1503
00:53:31,913 --> 00:53:34,323
- I'm terribly sorry.
- You must be tired.

1504
00:53:34,623 --> 00:53:36,183
- That was mean.
- It's really tiring.

1505
00:53:36,323 --> 00:53:37,553
Why would he target only me?

1506
00:53:38,023 --> 00:53:42,893
(In Round 2, they attack only Middle-aged Jong Min again.)

1507
00:53:42,993 --> 00:53:44,492
Jong Min, you're out.

1508
00:53:44,493 --> 00:53:46,639
- It ended quickly.
- Let all three of us sleep inside.

1509
00:53:46,663 --> 00:53:48,983
- It's not a bad idea.
- Let the three of us sleep inside.

1510
00:53:49,133 --> 00:53:50,672
I'm pretty sure Se Yoon is next.

1511
00:53:50,673 --> 00:53:51,673
(Current survivors: Se Yoon, DinDin, Seon Ho)

1512
00:53:51,674 --> 00:53:53,194
I'm 100 percent sure it'll be Se Yoon.

1513
00:53:55,043 --> 00:53:56,773
This is the final round.

1514
00:53:57,013 --> 00:53:58,443
Play fair and square.

1515
00:53:59,143 --> 00:54:00,182
Please.

1516
00:54:00,183 --> 00:54:02,242
(Who will be the one to smile at the end?)

1517
00:54:02,243 --> 00:54:04,312
One, two, three.

1518
00:54:04,313 --> 00:54:05,383
Turn the light off.

1519
00:54:06,423 --> 00:54:12,953
(The club landed right next to Se Yoon.)

1520
00:54:15,323 --> 00:54:16,833
Gosh, that's scary. My, it's scary.

1521
00:54:18,163 --> 00:54:21,433
(They get far away from Se Yoon for now.)

1522
00:54:25,703 --> 00:54:27,219
- What is he doing?
